@node Translating "MARInA, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Translating..."

    @{b}MARInA Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


        @{b} Translating@{ub}

        Please feel free to translate the Requester's messages and
        buttons.

        Send your translated but not in other ways modified Versions
        of the Rexx-Scripts back to me by EMail, so that I may
        include them in localized versions. The names of the
        translators will be included with the new Guide.
        Many thanks!


        @{b} Speech Samples@{ub}

        If you have downloaded and supplied the  bundle of
        MARInA-samples for the installation Process, then you may
        let MARInA Applications talk to you in natural
        female voice.

        As the name MARInA is female and even our AMIGA (spain, means
        girlfriend in english) is a very nice girl, I want the package
        to talk in a decent female voice.

        Feel free to make (or let a woman/girl speak) new samples
        with the same Sample-FileNames as delivered. So you may
        even translate MARInA's speech. The active Voice-Directory is
        located in

                   Locale:Voice/$LANGUAGE

        thus, switching the Locale-Preferences, MARInA will even have
        the correct voice samples for your preferred Language, provided,
        you have supplied the new samples with correct Sample-FileNames
        to the correct directory. If not, MARInA will still run but
        it will stop speaking until you will switch back to a present
        Language (deutsch only, actually).

        Sure, here, we all are interested in your new samples, too.
        Please feel free to post them to:

                    Aminet/util/wb/

                    MARInA_SamplesE.lha
                    for english samples, e.g.
____________________________________________________________________
@endnode


@node disclaimer "MARInA, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Disclaimer"

    @{b}MARInA Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


        @{b} Disclaimer@{ub}

        First of all, I'd like to thank God and my wife Monika,
        who has born our doughter Kerstin today, 17.3.1998, 18:19.
        I am so glad, I couldn't believe that a baby would arouse
        so much charm in me.

        ... although ...


        With  this  document I make no warranties or representations,
        either expressed  or  implied,  with  respect to the program
        described herein.

        The program  and  the  information presented herein is being
        supplied on an `as is'  basis  and  is  expressly subject to
        change without notice. Eventually appearing incompatibilities
        of any user's MARInA-properties due to those changes must
        be accepted as trade off for the enhancement of functionality
        as far as a new update packet will be installed.

        All MARInA-parts of the package must be spread together.
        The package must be kept in it's original compilation when
        it is copied to other machines. MARInA-parts are all 
        MARInA-Scrits as well as the MARInA Reference-table.
        They are representing the functional center of the packet.

        This is especially important for MARInA because it is a 
        "System" that may only work correctly when it has been 
        installed directly from the original archive. But I will
        be greatfully be cooperative in terms of exceptions to 
        this paragraph if cooperation will serve the progress of 
        the AMIGA-system. Exceptions will be available only
        in writing.

        The Package may only be used for commercial purposes
        with the  prior written permission of the author. 
        I will be of course grant the right for commercially
        trading the packet if a contractual agreement has been
        worked out.

        The entire risk  as to the use of the program and the
        information presented is assumed by the user. In no event
        will  I  be liable  for  direct, indirect, incidental, or
        consequential damages resulting from any claim arising out
        of the use of the  program  or  the  information  presented
        herein,  even if I have been advised of the possibilities
        of such damages (with respect to those advises, I will of
        course try to fix all software-bugs as soon as it is 
        possible for me, being only a shareware author).

        The reason for such a strict paragraph should be clear:
        Being a shareware author, I may not afford any special
        insurance for such cases, nor may I afford such efficient
        systemtests as may afford large companies, where a whole
        team does nothing else than systemtests. That there do 
        exist even big software-companies who use similar
        paragraphs, may in contrast not be accepted for 
        longer times.

        While the software is delivered as Rexx-Scripts, thus
        being out-handed as sourcecode, everyone, who will modify
        them, is fully responsible for the modified code. Such
        modified MARInA-Modules may only be released to the
        user-base with my prior written permission - the code
        must be sent to me for verification first in order to keep a
        cooperational-center for the project MARInA. It is allowed
        to run modified MARInA-Modules on own systems at your own
        risk.

        The software was tested thoroughly on my own systems and
        has proved properly in daily use. So, it was released
        with a clear conscience (whenever a release means testing
        if software will really keep foolproof).

        @{b}Note:@{ub}
        Hardware and Software, today, is almost so complex that
        in NO CASE 100 % functionality may be granted for each
        and every System. The one who would claim this for his
        product, is a charlatan!

        Despite of all... even the Titanic has sunk...
