@node Binaries "MARInA, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Binaries"

    @{b}MARInA Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


       @{b} The included binaries@{ub}

       Included with this package are the Binaries residing
       in the directory, which is assigned to MARInA_bin:

       These Binaries are freely available CLI-commands, which
       are almost all derived from  aminet/util/cli.

       I've included the appropriate documentations for the
       binaries, which are essential parts of MARInA. See
       the Help section of the MARInA-Archive's directory
       tree. The Documentations may be installed automatically
       with the installation-Script which should be started
       from this Guide.

       If you've got some of those binaries already or even
       newer versions, make an

           ASSIGN MARInA_bin: YourBinaryDir ADD

       in addition to the MARInA-Settings in S:USER-STARTUP.

       I'm not sure if every binary will work on your system,
       because I do often use the 68030,040,060 versions of the
       packages. In the case that your system will guru on this,
       just have an additional look into the aminet for the
       original binaries' archives.

       P.S.: Many Thanks to all authors who I could have violated
       their Disclaimer a little bit, but thanks for their great work!
       By this package, your work will be spread even more as you
       would have thought and it will become much worth to the
       community! The ShareWare Fee does only contain MARInA
       development Manpower and therefore does not contain any
       part for supplying external utilities.

       So, please consider the inclusion of the multiple CLI-
       utilities as a user-service, which is essential for MARInA
       to be releasable.


____________________________________________________________________
@endnode



